Wash and dry produce.

In a #small pot{}, combine @White Rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, trim and halve @Zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into 1/4-inch-thick half-moons. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Heat a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{4%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add zucchini and season with salt and @pepper{}.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes} (7-10 minutes for 4 servings). Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{} and tent with #foil{} to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

While zucchini cooks, pat pork dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper.

> Swap in chicken or beef for pork.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for zucchini over medium-high heat. Add @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

> Cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook beef to desired doneness, 5-7 minutes per side.

> Thinly slice chicken or beef against the grain.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for pork over medium-low heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @Red Pepper Jam{1}, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{2}, 1/4 cup water, and @Butter{1%tablespoon} (1/3 cup water and 2 TBSP butter for 4 servings); cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce has thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @Crème Fraîche{2%tablespoon} until combined. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Thinly slice pork crosswise.

Divide rice and zucchini between #plates{}. Top rice with pork and drizzle with pan sauce. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.